  "text": "To force the server to perform these operations correctly, we add Merkle hashing on top of the OPE Tree and use it to check the correctness of the server's responses. Merkle trees [CITATION_1] are a common method for enforcing integrity properties, so using them for integrity is not novel to this work; only the way we integrate it with our scheme is new. Fig. 7 shows the contents of an OPE Tree with Merkle hashes. The Merkle hash at a node is a hash over the data at this node and the Merkle hashes of its children.",
